{
  "Wave-Particle Duality": "波粒质量",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is wave-particle duality?": "什么是波粒的双重性?",
  "Wave-particle duality is a central concept of quantum mechanics: all quantum objects (photons, electrons, atoms) display both wave and particle behavior. Which aspect is observed depends on the experimental setup.": "波粒二元性是量子力学的一个核心概念:所有量子物体(磷、电子、原子)都显示波和粒子行为。观察到的哪个方面取决于实验设置。",
  "What is the de Broglie wavelength?": "布鲁格利波长是什么?",
  "The de Broglie wavelength lambda = h/p = h/(mv) assigns a wave character to all moving matter. De Broglie's 1924 hypothesis was confirmed by electron diffraction experiments in 1927.": "de Broglie波长 lambda = h/p = h/(mv) 指定所有移动物质的波字符。 De Broglie 1924年的假设得到了1927年电子折射实验的证实。",
  "What is the Heisenberg uncertainty principle?": "海森堡不确定原则是什么?",
  "The uncertainty principle is a fundamental limit of nature (not instrument limitations): the more precisely one knows a particle's position, the less precisely one can know its momentum, and vice versa.": "不确定性原则是性质的基本限制(而不是仪器限制):了解粒子位置的精确度越高,了解其动力的精确度就越低,反之亦然。",
  "What is Compton scattering?": "什么是康普顿分散?",
  "Compton scattering occurs when a photon collides with a free electron. The photon transfers some energy and momentum to the electron, emerging with a longer wavelength: delta_lambda = (h/mc)(1 - cos theta).": "当光子与自由电子相撞时, Compton 散射就会发生。 光子将一些能量和动力转移到电子, 以较长波长出现: delta_ lambda = (h/ mc) = (1 - cos theta ) 。",
  "What is a matter wave?": "什么是事件波?",
  "A matter wave (de Broglie wave) is the wave-like behavior of a particle. Its wavelength lambda = h/p determines how the particle diffracts and interferes. The wave function psi describes the probability of finding the particle.": "物质波(de Broglie 波) 是粒子的波状行为。 它的波长 lambda = h/p 来决定粒子 diffracts 和 干扰。 波函数 psi 描述找到粒子的概率 。",
  "What is a wave function?": "什么是波函数?",
  "The wave function psi(x,t) is a complex-valued function in quantum mechanics. |psi|^2 gives the probability density of finding the particle at position x at time t. It is obtained by solving the Schrodinger equation.": "波函数 psi( x, t) 是量子力学中一种复杂估值的函数 。 @ psi @% 2 给出了在时间 t 的方位 x 找到粒子的概率密度 。 它通过解析 Schrodyinger 方程式获得 。",
  "What is the Davisson-Germer experiment?": "Davisson -Germer实验是什么?",
  "Davisson and Germer (1927) fired electrons at a nickel crystal and observed diffraction peaks at angles predicted by de Broglie's wavelength formula, providing the first direct evidence for matter waves.": "Davisson和Germer(1927年)向镍晶体发射电子,并在De Broglie波长公式预测的角度观测到折射峰值,为物质波提供了第一批直接证据。",
  "What is the complementarity principle?": "什么是互补原则?",
  "Bohr's complementarity principle states that wave and particle aspects of quantum objects are complementary: a single experiment reveals one aspect or the other, never both simultaneously. Both are necessary for complete understanding.": "Bohr的互补原则指出,量子物体的波和粒子方面是相辅相成的:单项实验揭示一个方面或另一个方面,从不同时同时出现,两者都是完全理解所必须的。",
  "What is the Compton wavelength shift?": "什么是康普顿波长变化?",
  "The Compton shift delta_lambda = (h/(m_e*c))(1 - cos theta) describes how much a photon's wavelength increases when it scatters off an electron at angle theta. h/(m_e*c) = 0.00243 nm is the Compton wavelength of the electron.": "Compton  Shift delta_lambda = (h/(m_e*c) (1 - cos theta) 描述光子在角上散布电子时,光子的波长增加多少。 h/(m_e*c) = 0.00243 nm 是电子的光子波长。",
  "What is quantum tunneling?": "什么是量子隧道?",
  "Quantum tunneling occurs when a particle's wave function extends through a potential barrier, giving it a nonzero probability of appearing on the other side. It is crucial in nuclear fusion, semiconductor devices, and scanning tunneling microscopes.": "当粒子的波波功能通过潜在屏障延伸,使其在另一侧出现的可能性不为零时,就会产生量子隧道。 在核聚变、半导体装置和扫描隧道显微镜方面,这种技术至关重要。",
  "An electron is accelerated from rest through a 150 V potential difference. What is its de Broglie wavelength?": "电子从休息加速到150V 潜在差异。 它的布洛格里波长是多少?",
  "lambda = h/sqrt(2meV) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(2*9.11e-31*1.6e-19*150) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(4.37e-47) = 6.63e-34/6.61e-24 = 1.0e-10 m = 0.1 nm.": "lambda = h/sqrt(2meV) = 6.63e-34/sqrt (2*9.11e-31*1.6e-19*150) = 6.63e-34/sqrt (4.37e-47) = 6.63e-34/6.61e-24 = 1.0e-10m = 0.1nm。",
  "A neutron (mass 1.67 * 10^-27 kg) has a de Broglie wavelength of 0.14 nm. What is its kinetic energy?": "中子(质量1.67 * 10-27公斤)的脱溴波长为0.14纳米。 其动能是什么?",
  "p = h/lambda = 6.63e-34/(0.14e-9) = 4.74e-24 kg*m/s. KE = p^2/(2m) = (4.74e-24)^2/(2*1.67e-27) = 2.25e-47/3.34e-27 = 6.73e-21 J = 0.042 eV.": "p=h/lambda = 6.63e-34/(0.14e-9) = 4.74e-24kg*m/s. KE = p2/(2m) = (4.74e-244)/2(2.67e-27) = 2.25e-47/3.34e-27 = 6.73e-21J = 0.042 eV.",
  "In Compton scattering, an X-ray photon of wavelength 0.07 nm scatters off a free electron at 90 degrees. What is the wavelength of the scattered photon?": "在Compton散射中,波长为0.07纳米的X光光片在90度从自由电子中散射。散射光子的波长是多少?",
  "delta_lambda = (h/mc)(1-cos(90)) = 0.00243 nm * (1-0) = 0.00243 nm. lambda' = 0.07 + 0.00243 = 0.0724 nm.": "delta_lambda = (h/mc)(1-cos(90)) = 0.00243 nm * (1-0) = 0.0024 nm = 0.0024 nm. lambda = 0.07 + 0.0024 = 0.0724 nm.",
  "A 70 kg person walks at 1.5 m/s. What is their de Broglie wavelength?": "70公斤的人在1.5米/秒时行走。",
  "lambda = h/(mv) = 6.63e-34/(70*1.5) = 6.63e-34/105 = 6.3 * 10^-36 m. This is incredibly small - far too small to observe, which is why macroscopic objects don't exhibit wave behavior.": "lambda = h/(mv) = 6.63e-34/(70*1.5) = 6.63e-34/105 = 6.3 * 10-36米。这非常小,太小,无法观察,这就是为什么大型物体不表现出波状行为的原因。",
  "An electron is confined to a region of width 0.1 nm (approximately the size of an atom). What is the minimum uncertainty in its velocity?": "电子局限于宽度为0.1纳米(约等于原子大小)的区域。 其速度的最小不确定性是什么?",
  "delta_p >= h-bar/(2*delta_x) = (1.055e-34)/(2*0.1e-9) = 5.28e-25 kg*m/s. delta_v = delta_p/m = 5.28e-25/9.11e-31 = 5.8*10^5 m/s.": "delta_p  h-bar/ (2*delta_x) = (1.055e-34)/ (2*0.1e-9) = 5.28e-25kg*s. delta_v = delta_p/m = 5.28e-25/9.11e-31 = 5.8*105m/s。",
  "An electron microscope uses electrons accelerated through 50,000 V. What is the de Broglie wavelength of these electrons, and how does it compare to visible light?": "电子显微镜使用通过50 000 V加速的电子。 这些电子的布洛格利波长是多少,它与可见光的光相比如何?",
  "lambda = h/sqrt(2meV) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(2*9.11e-31*1.6e-19*50000) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(1.46e-44) = 6.63e-34/1.21e-22 = 5.5e-12 m = 0.0055 nm. This is ~100,000 times shorter than visible light, enabling much higher resolution.": "lambda = h/sqrt(2meV) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(29.11e-31*1.6e-19*5000) = 6.63e-34/sqrt(1.46e-44) = 6.63e-34/1.21e-22 = 5.5e-12m =0.0055纳米,比可见光短100 000倍,分辨率高得多。",
  "In a scanning tunneling microscope, electrons tunnel across a gap of 1 nm. If the barrier height is 4 eV, what is the approximate transmission probability factor for the exponential decay?": "在扫描隧道显微镜中,电子隧道的距离为1纳米。如果屏障高度为4 eV,那么指数衰减的大致传输概率系数是什么?",
  "The decay constant kappa = sqrt(2mU)/h-bar = sqrt(2*9.11e-31*4*1.6e-19)/(1.055e-34) = sqrt(1.166e-48)/1.055e-34 = 1.08e-24/1.055e-34 = 1.024e10 /m. For d = 1 nm: 2*kappa*d = 2*1.024e10*1e-9 = 20.5. T ∝ e^-20.5 ≈ 1.2*10^-9.": "衰变常数 kappa = sqrt (2mU)/h-bar = sqrt (2*9.11e-31*4*1.6e-19)/(1.055e-34) = sqrt (1.166e-48)/1.055e-34 = 1.08e-24/1.055e-34 = 1.024e-10/m。对于 d = 1 nm: 2 *kappa *d = 2 *1.024e10*1e-9 = 20.5, T = e-20.5 *1.2*10-9。"
}